{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For the FH radar, each pulse can be divided into several subpulses, which facilitates the implementation of various fast time modulation strategies.",
    "For example, Eedara et al. [152] embedded the communication symbols into the FH signal in each sub-pulse via PM.",
    "In addition, the FH code selection in each subpulse can also be used to convey the communication message [97,153].",
    "Xu et al. [47] proposed a hybrid IM-based signaling scheme for the FH radar, where the communication symbols were represented by the indices of 3-tuples in a hybrid dictionary.",
    "However, the fast time modulation strategy introduces more randomness into the original radar waveform, leading to the degradation of the sensing capability."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
